            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The trick that deoplete uses is to first use `echom` for additional info (traceback), then `redraw` and then `echom` for the main msg.\r\nThis way you have it in `:messages`, but are not bothered with the full blob initially.\r\nI've noticed that this does not work as expected when using `vim.err_write`.",
